The **Plane of Earth** is the first of the [Elemental Planes](/wiki/Elemental_Planes "Elemental Planes"). It is reached by going up from the top level of the [Dungeons of Doom](/wiki/Dungeons_of_Doom "Dungeons of Doom") while carrying the [Amulet of Yendor](/wiki/Amulet_of_Yendor "Amulet of Yendor") - after this point, the Dungeons of Doom become permanently inaccessible to the [hero](/wiki/Hero "Hero"), and they must make their way towards their goal of the [Astral Plane](/wiki/Astral_Plane "Astral Plane").

The Plane of Earth is ineligible to leave [bones](/wiki/Bones "Bones") files. The entire level is no-teleport and has a [non-diggable](/wiki/Non-diggable "Non-diggable") floor.

[ ]

- [2 Strategy](#Strategy)

Most of the level is filled with solid rock around caverns that are scattered as shown above, including single-square areas placed randomly on the level. The hero will enter the level in the bottom-right cavern, and the [magic portal](/wiki/Magic_portal "Magic portal") to the [Plane of Air](/wiki/Plane_of_Air "Plane of Air") is randomly placed in one of the other caverns.

The entrance cavern contains a [minotaur](/wiki/Minotaur "Minotaur") with a guaranteed [wand of digging](/wiki/Wand_of_digging "Wand of digging") and an [Elvenking](/wiki/Elvenking "Elvenking") with a guaranteed [pick-axe](/wiki/Pick-axe "Pick-axe"), and upon entering the level, the [Wizard of Yendor](/wiki/Wizard_of_Yendor "Wizard of Yendor") will immediately appear before the hero carrying a [spellbook of dig](/wiki/Spellbook_of_dig "Spellbook of dig") (resurrecting if necessary).[\[1\]](#cite_note-1)[\[2\]](#cite_note-2)[\[3\]](#cite_note-3) The remainder of the level contains 27 [earth elementals](/wiki/Earth_elemental "Earth elemental"), eight [rock trolls](/wiki/Rock_troll "Rock troll"), five [stone giants](/wiki/Stone_giant "Stone giant"), five [pit vipers](/wiki/Pit_viper "Pit viper"), three [barbed devils](/wiki/Barbed_devil "Barbed devil"), three [pit fiends](/wiki/Pit_fiend "Pit fiend"), a [rock piercer](/wiki/Rock_piercer "Rock piercer"), an [umber hulk](/wiki/Umber_hulk "Umber hulk"), a [dust vortex](/wiki/Dust_vortex "Dust vortex"), four [stone golems](/wiki/Stone_golem "Stone golem"), a [scorpion](/wiki/Scorpion "Scorpion"), and a second minotaur, distributed fairly evenly among the caverns.

Digging with a pick-axe or dwarvish mattock has a 1⁄3 chance of generating [earth elementals](/wiki/Earth_elemental "Earth elemental") and [xorns](/wiki/Xorn "Xorn").[\[4\]](#cite_note-4) Digging with blessed tools also has a 1⁄3 chance of a 3x3 area of rock immediately clearing around the hero[\[5\]](#cite_note-5) - otherwise, digging with tools has a 1⁄6 chance of a cave-in creating walls in that same area if the tool is uncursed, and a 1⁄4 chance of doing so if the tool is cursed.

## Strategy

The Plane of Earth is the most straightforward of the planes. Once the Wizard has been dispatched, the primary challenge is quickly locating the portal.

### Moving

The single wand of digging dropped by the minotaur may not be sufficient to reach the portal, especially if exploration is required. Bringing a few wands of your own or a source of [charging](/wiki/Charging "Charging") is strongly recommended, and there should be several available by the time you are ready to enter the Planes. If you find that you must use digging tools to clear a path, make sure to bless them in order to potentially speed up progress.

### Surviving

Most of the monsters should pose no real threat to an ascension-worthy character. However, the many earth elementals on the Plane will [phase](/wiki/Phase "Phase") through the solid rock to get to you, and can impede progress if you dig too slowly; they are also generated with 3 times the HP of those encountered in the dungeons.[\[6\]](#cite_note-6) [Conflict](/wiki/Conflict "Conflict") can help if you are surrounded, as does [polymorphing](/wiki/Polymorphing "Polymorphing") into a phasing monster yourself, which will enable you to move around rapidly - the usual polyselfing caveats to those forms apply.

### Portal detection

The portal can be located by the [usual methods](/wiki/Portal_detection_methods "Portal detection methods")—[scroll of gold detection](/wiki/Scroll_of_gold_detection "Scroll of gold detection"), [wand of secret door detection](/wiki/Wand_of_secret_door_detection "Wand of secret door detection"), spell of [detect unseen](/wiki/Spellbook_of_detect_unseen "Spellbook of detect unseen"), wearing the Amulet of Yendor, and so on. Reading a [cursed](/wiki/Cursed "Cursed") [scroll of gold detection](/wiki/Scroll_of_gold_detection "Scroll of gold detection") is the fastest and easiest—just remember where it was, because it will become invisible when you get near. Non-cursed scrolls also work if the hero has a source of [confusion](/wiki/Confusion "Confusion") - players lacking a source may consider seeking out the umber hulk in the center of the level, which also makes it possible to enter the [Plane of Air](/wiki/Plane_of_Air "Plane of Air") confused as well. If all else fails, it is possible (though much slower) to locate the portal by visiting each cavern and searching or walking over every square - having the [automatic searching](/wiki/Automatic_searching "Automatic searching") property can easily assist in this regard.

## Messages

- The debris from your digging comes to life!

  Earth elementals and/or xorns were generated from digging using a pick-axe or dwarvish mattock.

- A mysterious force \<creates a/extends the> cave around you!

  An opening was created by digging with a blessed pick.

- Crash! The ceiling collapses around you!

  Walls were generated from digging with a non-blessed pick.
